_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa057c4ca-f34f-4bd0-b9ec-1c6dda67854a_936x574.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa057c4ca-f34f-4bd0-b9ec-1c6dda67854a_936x574.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Source: <a href="https://www.brookings.edu/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/1_Case-Deaton_unembargoed.pdf">Case &amp; Deaton (2023)</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> <a href="https://jabberwocking.com/rising-mortality-is-mostly-limited-to-white-high-school-dropouts/">Kevin Drum points out</a> that this emerging gap is mostly among White Americans.</p><p> Now, when you see changes like this, you always want to think about composition effects. Over time, more and more Americans have gotten college degrees </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe266b306-96b9-4594-b1bd-301f83da396f_787x621.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe266b306-96b9-4594-b1